node.text:
We’re changing, me and you.
I’m learning and you’re teaching.
You’re patient while I’m steady.

We’re growing, me and you.
Through deep nights and messy days.
Through hard feeds and smiling eyes.

We’re thriving, me and you.
Yes me, and all my uncertainty.
And you with your trust and gentle surrender.

We’re doing this, me and you. 
Day after day.
Night after sweet night.
Yes, my baby, we got this. 

Words: @mia_carr_
Image: @teresadoesit

The greatest, most powerful force in all this world is a gentle mother. 
A whirl of fierce and vulnerable love, focused in on her babies. 
Light in this dark, the mama stands still and strong. 
She never dims for these babies, though she may feel it. 
She’s the warmth, the life and the sun they all revolve.
